===Etymology===
{{L.}} from {{Gk.}} ''[[ορχήστρα]]'' ''orch&#275;stra'' from ορχή ''orchi''

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''orchestra'''
# {{music}} A large [[group]] of [[musicians]] who [[play]] together on [[various]] [[instrument]]s, usually including [[strings]], [[woodwind]], [[brass]] and [[percussion]]; the instruments played by such a group.
# The [[area]] in a [[theatre]] or [[concert hall]] where the musicians sit, [[immediately]] in front of and below the [[stage]].
# A [[semicircular]] [[space]] in front of the stage used by the [[chorus]] in [[ancient]] [[Greek]] theatres.

